	   		<div class="col460 clear">
	       		<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/39ece444504f8db7c07c1a6c42345a82?s=50&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D50&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-50 photo' height='50' width='50' />	   				   			<blockquote><p>I’m curious why you chose to describe this as “adultism” and not “ageism”.</p></blockquote>
<p>A rectangle is not a square, but a square is a rectangle. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ageism" rel="nofollow">Ageism</a> certainly encompasses <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adultism" rel="nofollow">adultism</a> but is nevertheless distinct from it. I also maintain that while there are overlaps between discrimination against the very old and the very young, the young are a more distressed group in more areas, not just sexuality, than the old. And on a personal note, I have been very young before, but I have not yet been very old. :)</p>
	   		</div>
