   	<li class="clear" id="comment-25312">
    	<div class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 clear">
	   		<div class="col140">
	   				   			<p>by <strong>Beka</strong></p>
	   			<p><strong>10 Dec 2009</strong> at <a href="#comment-25312">10:04</a></p>
	   				   				   		</div>
	   		
	   		<div class="col460 clear">
	       		<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/dda6d7bdf2dc853a0a696ee7d0904940?s=50&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D50&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-50 photo' height='50' width='50' />	   				   			<p>Wow.  Just&#8230; thank you.  I&#8217;m 23 years old and still dealing with the pain and closeted sexuality issues that I developed when I was a kid, because I wasn&#8217;t allowed to make my own decisions.  I wasn&#8217;t allowed to go to my school&#8217;s sex ed class because it was &#8220;inappropriate&#8221; (our school required parents to sign a permission slip for kids to go to the sex ed classes, and mine wouldn&#8217;t).  My only source of information, like you, was the internet and my parents&#8217; AOL account, but by the time I found it, parental controls were extremely restrictive, and they could (and did) change the password on my account multiple times, when I was being &#8220;punished&#8221; and not allowed to use the computer.  I got in trouble for going to pornographic websites when I just wanted to know a) what sex really entailed, and b) what the big deal was.</p>
<p>When I was 16, I told a 25-year-old man that I was a 19-year-old journalism student at the local college so that he&#8217;d flirt with me, and kiss me, just so I could silently and secretly defy my parents and express the sexuality I knew I had but was told was wrong &#8212; and then found myself too terrified to tell him I wasn&#8217;t comfortable with going further and had sex when I wasn&#8217;t emotionally ready for it.  Two months later, after many promises that she wouldn&#8217;t tell anyone, I told my camp counsellor that I&#8217;d had sex and that I felt guilty about it.  She told me God would forgive me for sinning, then told her boss, who told my parents.  They took away my bedroom door, removing any privacy that I&#8217;d managed to scrape together.</p>
<p>Sorry to go on, just&#8230; this IS a huge problem &#8211; kids should not NEED to be emancipated.  They should be free already.</p>
	   		</div>
   		</div>
