<p>&#8220;I don’t want any other young person to go through the isolation and uncertainty I felt about my own sexuality at that age. Do you?&#8221;</p>
<p>NO. </p>
<p>I don&#8217;t want them feeling like they&#8217;re going to hell for having sexual fantasies of people of the same gender, or that any kind of birth control is pointless because it&#8217;s an act of admitting shame and if they catch something it&#8217;s all God&#8217;s punishment and vengeance for having sex which they shouldn&#8217;t have been doing in the first place. </p>
<p>I don&#8217;t want anyone sticking tampons up their ass because they don&#8217;t know where their own proper damn body parts are or thinking that they lost their virginity when a boy stuck his hand down their shirt because of that stupid Madonna song &#8220;touched for the very first time.&#8221; </p>
<p><a href="http://sunshinegypsy.com/2009/04/17/protect-the-children/" rel="nofollow">http://sunshinegypsy.com/2009/04/17/protect-the-children/</a></p>
<p>I don&#8217;t want them getting date raped over and over again as a teenager because the abusive adultist FUCKS in their life taught them that it was never okay to say &#8220;no&#8221; and that your only chance of salvation is to be obedient and unquestioning. </p>
<p>I especially don&#8217;t want anyone to ever have to feel like less (or a different kind) of a person simply for having a sexual body at an early age, or worse, that they asked for it, or that they&#8217;re asking for anything else because of it. And if they are asking for anything else, then they shouldn&#8217;t have it taken from them or displayed as a thing to be ashamed of. </p>
<p>Fuck. /rant</p>
